  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `1.6.6`\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nWe set `--gasprice` to 0, and expect that we can accept transactions with 0 gasprice.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nFail to accept transactions with 0 gasprice if we set `--gasprice` to 0, but success if we set `--txpool.pricelimit` to 0.\r\n\r\n```\r\n--gasprice \"18000000000\"  Minimal gas price to accept for mining a transactions\r\n--txpool.pricelimit value    Minimum gas price limit to enforce for acceptance into the pool (default: 1)\r\n```\r\n\r\nDo these two flags define the same attribute? If so, I can fire a PR to combine these two flags.",
