    "body": "They are not exactly the same. The `txpool.pricelimit` defines a baseline transaction price under which the node will simply not accept transactions (not even for forwarding). The `gasprice` flag is only used during mining, but if you do enable mining, it overwrites the former price limit to enforce that only \"mineable\" transactions end up in your pool.",
